p: In obedience to the within writ I have the body of Eleck Loan here in open court and for my return say that he was commited to my custody on the 25th day of October 1856 by virtue of a warrant issued by Justice Johnson on charge of being a runaway slave which warrant of commmit to is here anexd and made a part of this return
Habeas Corpus in the matter of Eleck Loan
